INSTALL 
-------------------------------------------------
1. From source:: 

   $ python setup.py build 
   $ python setup.py install 


2. From packages 

Debian:
   - Create repository file /etc/apt/sources.list.d/teddix.list:

       # teddix repository
       deb http://repo.teddix.info/debian wheezy unstable

   - apt-get install package 


Fedora:

   - Create repository file /etc/yum.repos.d/teddix.repo:

      [teddix]
      name=Teddix official repository
      baseurl=http://repo.teddix.info/redhat/fedora/$releasever/$basearch
      gpgcheck=0
      enabled=1

   - yum install package


CONFIGURATION  
-------------------------------------------------
1. Agent 

   - edit /etc/teddix/teddix.conf

2. Server  

   - Database configuration: 
   	CREATE DATABASE teddix;  
   	CREATE USER 'teddix'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'mypass';  
   	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON teddix.* To 'teddix'@'localhost'; 

   - Import tables: 
   	$ mysql -u root < /usr/share/teddix/initdb.sql 

   - edit /etc/teddix/teddix.conf

2. Web frontend  

   - edit /etc/teddix/websettings.py 
   
   - start fcgi: 
   	$ cd /usr/share/teddix-web/ && python ./manage.py runfcgi method=threaded host=127.0.0.1 port=8000

   - configure webserver to use fcgi: 
   	https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/howto/deployment/fastcgi/
   
   	(example for nginx: https://code.djangoproject.com/wiki/DjangoAndNginx) 
       

